Extracting important features from the Raw Data¶

1) Tweet volume

In [553]:
#Getting tweet volume column
btc_raw_data_eng["Datetime"]=pd.to_datetime(btc_raw_data_eng["Datetime"])
btc_raw_data_eng["Date"]=pd.to_datetime(btc_raw_data_eng["Datetime"]).dt.date
#fico_region_avg_fico= fico_with_region.groupby(['region']).agg({'FICO':'mean'}).reset_index()

#Volume of tweets
day_level_btc_raw_data_eng=btc_raw_data_eng.groupby('Date')['Tweet Id'].count().reset_index()
day_level_btc_raw_data_eng.columns=["Date", "tweet_volume"]

2) Tweets above 0/1/10/100/1000 likes

In [554]:
#Getting perc_Tweets_above_0/1/10/100/1000_like
btc_raw_data_eng["likeCount"]=pd.to_numeric(btc_raw_data_eng["likeCount"])

btc_raw_data_eng["likes_greater_than_0"]=np.where(btc_raw_data_eng["likeCount"]>0,1,0)
btc_raw_data_eng["likes_greater_than_1"]=np.where(btc_raw_data_eng["likeCount"]>1,1,0)
btc_raw_data_eng["likes_greater_than_10"]=np.where(btc_raw_data_eng["likeCount"]>10,1,0)
btc_raw_data_eng["likes_greater_than_100"]=np.where(btc_raw_data_eng["likeCount"]>100,1,0)
btc_raw_data_eng["likes_greater_than_1000"]=np.where(btc_raw_data_eng["likeCount"]>1000,1,0)

likes_count= btc_raw_data_eng.groupby(['Date']).agg({'likes_greater_than_0':'sum','likes_greater_than_1':'sum','likes_greater_than_10':'sum','likes_greater_than_100':'sum','likes_greater_than_1000':'sum'}).reset_index()

3) Retweet count per day

In [555]:
#Perc_Retweet_count
btc_raw_data_eng["retweetCount"]=pd.to_numeric(btc_raw_data_eng["retweetCount"])
btc_raw_data_eng["retweetCount_greater_than_0"]=np.where(btc_raw_data_eng["retweetCount"]>0,1,0)
retweet_count_to_get_perc=btc_raw_data_eng.groupby(['Date']).agg({'retweetCount_greater_than_0':'sum'}).reset_index()

4) Day of the week feature

In [556]:
#Getting day of the week
day_level_btc_raw_data_eng['day_of_week']=pd.to_datetime(day_level_btc_raw_data_eng['Date']).dt.day_name()

5) Distinct users

In [557]:
#Getting Distinct users
Distinct_users=btc_raw_data_eng.groupby('Date')['Username'].nunique().reset_index()
Distinct_users.columns=["Date", "distinct_users"]

6) Time of day

In [558]:
#Getting Time of day
btc_raw_data_eng["hour_of_day"]= btc_raw_data_eng["Datetime"].dt.hour
btc_raw_data_eng["hour_of_day_0_6"]=np.where(btc_raw_data_eng["hour_of_day"]<6,1,0)
btc_raw_data_eng["hour_of_day_6_12"]=np.where((btc_raw_data_eng["hour_of_day"]>5) & (btc_raw_data_eng["hour_of_day"]<12),1,0)
btc_raw_data_eng["hour_of_day_12_18"]=np.where((btc_raw_data_eng["hour_of_day"]>11) & (btc_raw_data_eng["hour_of_day"]<18),1,0)
btc_raw_data_eng["hour_of_day_18_24"]=np.where((btc_raw_data_eng["hour_of_day"]>17) & (btc_raw_data_eng["hour_of_day"]<24),1,0)
hour_of_day= btc_raw_data_eng.groupby(['Date']).agg({'hour_of_day_0_6':'sum','hour_of_day_6_12':'sum','hour_of_day_12_18':'sum','hour_of_day_18_24':'sum'}).reset_index()

#Merging -Skipping sentiment analysis file

    day_level_btc_raw_data_eng=pd.merge(day_level_btc_raw_data_eng,

def mean_absolute_percentage_error(y_true, y_pred): 
    y_true, y_pred = np.array(y_true), np.array(y_pred)
    return np.mean(np.abs((y_true - y_pred) / y_true)) * 100

#Implementing cross validation
from sklearn.model_selection import KFold
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
x_needed_cols=['tweet_volume', 'likes_greater_than_0','likes_greater_than_1', 'likes_greater_than_10','likes_greater_than_100', 'likes_greater_than_1000', 'distinct_users','hour_of_day_0_6', 'hour_of_day_6_12', 'hour_of_day_12_18','hour_of_day_18_24', 'retweet_perc','Btc_current_price', 'Volume','day__Friday', 'day__Monday','day__Saturday', 'day__Sunday', 'day__Thursday', 'day__Tuesday','day__Wednesday']
#'Close', 'Volume']
X = raw_data_for_classification.loc[:, x_needed_cols]
y = raw_data_for_classification.loc[:, ['price_high_low_class']]

k = 5
kf = KFold(n_splits=k, random_state=None)
#model = LogisticRegression(solver= 'liblinear')
#model = DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion = 'entropy', random_state = 0)

import xgboost as xgb
model = xgb.XGBClassifier(objective="binary:logistic", random_state=42)
acc_score = []

for train_index , test_index in kf.split(X):
    X_train, X_test = X.iloc[train_index], X.iloc[test_index]
    y_train , y_test = y.iloc[train_index] , y.iloc[test_index]
    model.fit(X_train,y_train)
    pred_values = model.predict(X_test)
     
    acc = accuracy_score(pred_values , y_test)
    acc_score.append(acc)
     
avg_acc_score = sum(acc_score)/k
 
print('accuracy of each fold - {}'.format(acc_score))
print('Avg accuracy : {}'.format(avg_acc_score))
 

accuracy of each fold - [0.49295774647887325, 0.5, 0.5428571428571428, 0.4714285714285714, 0.5428571428571428]

from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve
from sklearn.metrics import auc

# Compute fpr, tpr, thresholds and roc auc
fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred)
roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)

# Plot ROC curve
plt.figure(figsize=(20,8))
plt.plot(fpr_knn,tpr_knn,label='KNN (area = %0.3f)' % roc_auc_knn,linewidth=6)
plt.plot(fpr_lr,tpr_lr,label='Logistic Reg (area = %0.3f)' % roc_auc_lr,linewidth=6)
plt.plot(fpr_naive_b,tpr_naive_b,label='Naive Bayes (area = %0.3f)' % roc_auc_naive_b,linewidth=6)
plt.plot(fpr_ksvm,tpr_ksvm,label='Kernel-SVM (area = %0.3f)' % roc_auc_ksvm,linewidth=6)
plt.plot(fpr_svm,tpr_svm,label='SVM (area = %0.3f)' % roc_auc_svm,linewidth=6)
plt.plot(fpr_dtree,tpr_dtree,label='Decision Tree (area = %0.3f)' % roc_auc_dtree,linewidth=6)
plt.plot(fpr_rf,tpr_rf,label='Random Forest (area = %0.3f)' % roc_auc_rf,linewidth=6)
plt.plot(fpr_dnn,tpr_dnn,label='DNN (area = %0.3f)' % roc_auc_dnn,linewidth=6)
plt.plot(fpr_xgb,tpr_xgb,label='XG-Boost (area = %0.3f)' % roc_auc_xgb,linewidth=6)
plt.plot(fpr_ensemble,tpr_ensemble,label='Ensemble - LGBM+XGB+KNN (area = %0.3f)' % roc_auc_ensemble,linewidth=6)
plt.plot(fpr_lgbm,tpr_lgbm,label='Light GBM (area = %0.3f)' % roc_auc_lgbm,linewidth=6)

plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')  # random predictions curve
plt.xlim([0.0, 1.0])
plt.ylim([0.0, 1.0])
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate or (1 - Specifity)',fontsize=22)
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate or (Sensitivity)',fontsize=22)
plt.title('Receiver Operating Characteristic',fontsize=30)
#plt.legend(loc="lower right",fontsize=18)
plt.legend(fontsize=14)
